step.reason:
 \dfrac{5x}{(x+1)(x^2 -4)}= \dfrac{A}{x+1} + \dfrac{B}{x+2} + \dfrac{C}{x -2}\\
\implies 5x = A(x^2-4) + B(x+1)(x-2) \\
\qquad \qquad  \qquad \; \;  \qquad + C(x+1)(x+2) \\
\qquad \quad  \qquad = (A+B+C)x^2 + (-B+3C)x \\
\qquad \quad  \qquad +(-2A-B+C)\\
\text{On comparing coefficients, we get}\\
A+B+C = 0 , \, -B+3C=5 , \, -2A-B+C=0 \\
\text{Solve to get }
A= \dfrac{5}{3} , \, B = \dfrac{-5}{2} \text{ and }
C = \dfrac{5}{6}
